SIMPLE: intermediary
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intermediary
<hw>In`ter*me"di*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>interm⟦eacute⟧diaire</ets>.]</ety> <def>Lying, coming, or done,
between; intermediate; <as>as, an <ex>intermediary</ex>
project</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Intermediary amputation</b></col> <fld>(Surg.)</fld>,
<cd>an amputation for injury, performed after inflammation has set
in.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intermediary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Intermediary
<hw>In`ter*me"di*a*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Intermediaries</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>One who, or that
which, is intermediate; an interagent; a go-between; a
mediator.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intermediate</ent>⟦br⟧
